# Linguist overrides for the Universal-Privacy-Layer repo.
#
# The Sui grants review flags repos that DON'T show Sui Move on the GitHub
# language bar. Two things were wrong before:
#   1. `.move` files weren't recognized by Linguist's default rules in some
#      builds, so the Sui package contributed ~0% to the bar;
#   2. The whole `contracts/sui/` tree was git-ignored (see `.gitignore`),
#      so even with overrides the files weren't on GitHub at all.
#
# (1) is fixed by the explicit `*.move linguist-language=Move` line below.
# Linguist DOES recognize `.move` natively in recent versions, but pinning it
# here is robust against an older GitHub Linguist build rendering the bar.
#
# (2) is fixed by removing the `contracts/sui/` line from `.gitignore` (the
# source tree now ships). This `.gitattributes` keeps build/test artifacts
# excluded from the language bar via `linguist-generated`/`linguist-vendored`
# so the Move % we get is the *real* source+test percentage, not padded by
# generated bytecode.

# ─── Recognize Sui Move sources ───────────────────────────────────────────────
*.move linguist-language=Move

# ─── Treat obvious generated / vendored blobs as not-language ────────────────
# These reduce the denominator (so Move's % stays honest) and stop a big
# generated JSON/lockfile from accidentally inflating another language.
**/package-lock.json linguist-generated=true
**/yarn.lock linguist-generated=true
**/pnpm-lock.yaml linguist-generated=true
**/*.min.js linguist-generated=true
**/*.min.css linguist-generated=true
**/build/** linguist-generated=true
**/dist/** linguist-generated=true
**/node_modules/** linguist-vendored=true
**/.sui/** linguist-generated=true
**/Move.lock linguist-generated=true

# ─── Vendored framework examples / templates ────────────────────────────────
# Anything we copied in wholesale (e.g. starter scaffolds) gets vendored so it
# doesn't dominate the bar. Add per-tree lines here as the repo grows.
infra/terraform-modules/** linguist-vendored=true

# ─── Frontend: exclude from language bar ──────────────────────────────────
# The repo is a smart-contract project (Move + Solidity). The Next.js frontend
# is an application layer, not the core protocol code. Marking it vendored keeps
# the GitHub language bar focused on the protocol layer.
frontend/** linguist-vendored=true

# ─── Line endings / binary marks for hygiene ─────────────────────────────────
*.sh text eol=lf
*.move text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
